The course is a practical training of translating professional texts from English, German, French or Russian into Estonian and vice versa. The course is obligatory to the master's students of conference and written interpretation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the skills of translating LSP-texts on  law from the foreign language into Estonian. During the seminars, students  learn different translation strategies and methods for achieving the aim of the translation task. Students enhance their command of  terminology in Estonian as well as in the foreign language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course you have acquired the skills of analysis of LSP-texts on  law  in Estonian and the foreign language.
- Depending on text analysis results, you are able to choose the appropriate translation strategy for carrying out the translation task.
- You are able to find the necessary information for translation, to work with parallel texts and Internet databases.
